Happy 50th Birthday Hip Hop 🎶🎉

Blessed to have been there to witness & take part in a pivotal moment in hip hop— the naming of the street in the Bronx where it was born. If you don’t know, ppl thought hip hop would die out like disco or alternative music, but HA, look at it now! 50 yrs strong & the most streamed genre in the world 💪🏼🙏🏼

STORY TIME: My exposure to hip hop came from music videos. I was 8, we had just gotten cable (which was a big deal back then) & “Shoop” by  Salt-N—Pepa 👑 came on MTV and it was the first hip hop song I ever heard. (This came full circle for me when I intved them on Ladies First 🥹. ) I didn’t fully understand the song or the video I was watching except that I thought it looked cool, I loved how the timing of their words matched the beat (what I later learned as a flow), & the hook was mad catchy to me as an 8 year old. And then the You’re All I Need video came out… that was it for me. I remember the moment vividly. I thought the song was 🔥 and Meth and Mary looked so fn swaggy. From that point on, I started getting an allowance and saved my money to cop The Score, and The Coming from The Wiz. Then I stopped buying albums bc I was getting them “free 99” from those BMG buy now pay later pamphlets they used to do lmao 

All this to say the music holds a special place in my heart like it does for so many others!! 

Hip hop, I’ve loved you since I could remember, your music got me through the good & bad times, you’ve changed my life, gave me a career. No matter where I am in life, you’ll always be my first love 🤍🎶🙏🏼
 
#hiphop50 #hiphopmusic

💕🗣️: The premiere episode of @liteupladies new podcast “#WomenandWeed” is out featuring  @cannabaeofficial of @weedmaps. Her story is a JOURNEY. She’s been through the trenches, literally lived on a weed farm in the California Hills (IYKYK), and she’s a seasoned veteran in the cannabis community. I had such a great time chopping it up w her, listening to her insights and experiences as a woman in the cannabis world. The convo reaffirmed to me that you really don’t know what ppl have gone through and to not judge a book by it’s cover. And honey, lemme tell you, homegirl has been through and done A LOT. 

This podcast is not just to share amazing weed stories (which are always fun lol) but to show how respectable and lucrative the business is. The stigmas surrounding cannabis especially when it comes to women using it recreationally or making it a career, is an old ass dated one. My goal is to help elevate this narrative……in the JEN way ofc 😉

SN: my hair is looking nuts and my skin is glowing from the ridiculous amount of sweat I had from running around making sure the event was on point 😂

Shouts to my sis @crystalcaines_ for the beat 🎶

Shouts to my lil bro @hiphopmike for the cams 📹
 

Check out the full episode in my bio 🔗💨
